  <h4>Configure a local user account to run the PDF Generator service </h4> 
  <p>A local user account is required to run the PDF Generator service. For steps to create a local user, see <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/13951/windows-create-user-account" target="_blank">Create a user account in Windows</a> or <a href="https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-US/Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux/4/html/Step_by_Step_Guide/s1-starting-create-account.html" target="_blank">create a user account in UNIX-based platforms</a>.<br /> </p> 
  <ol> 
   <li><p>Open the <a href="http://localhost:4502/libs/fd/pdfg/config/ui.html" target="_blank">AEM Forms PDF Generator Configuration</a> page. <br /> <br /> </p> </li> 
   <li><p>In the <strong>User Accounts</strong> tab, provide credentials of a local user account, and click <strong>Submit</strong>. If Microsoft Windows prompts, allow access to the user. When added successfully, the configured user is displayed under the <strong>Your user accounts</strong> section in the <strong>User Accounts</strong> tab.</p> </li>    
  </ol> 
